    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, **Jackson Merrill** stands out as the anchor of the Austin Waves lineup with a 67.37 efficiency score. Even with the daunting prospect of facing Luis Castillo, **Merrill** benefits from a strong projected slot in the two-hole and a favorable dynamic platoon advantage (+13%), making him our most reliable play. Close behind is **Jacob Wilson** (62.77), who earns a significant boost from a combination of a hitter-friendly venue (+10% park factor) and a favorable matchup against Leiter, whose 4.43 xERA provides the highest ceiling for our hitters today. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (61.04) and **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (59.95) round out a balanced offensive core, with **Guerrero Jr.** anchored by his elite .384 xwOBA, proving his floor remains stable even against tougher pitching.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision today involved **Brady House**, who sat just outside the starting threshold with a 47.22 score. While he presents an intriguing profile against Ashcraft, his efficiency was suppressed by an elite opposing pitcher profile and his inability to match the combined categorical stability of **Miguel Vargas** or **Josh Jung**. Meanwhile, we must exercise caution with **Gunnar Henderson**. While he remains a core part of our roster, his score of 47.79 is hampered by a significant platoon disadvantage and a 44% rain risk in his matchup against Messick. We will monitor the weather closely; should the game face a delay, we are prepared to pivot to the bench, though for now, **Gunnar Henderson** remains in the lineup due to his high-leverage utility.",
